#: ../../../release_details/9.5/fluentReaderImprovements.md:1
msgid "Add zone section selection to FLUENT Reader"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/fluentReaderImprovements.md:3
msgid ""
"You can now select the zone sections you wish to load when reading a FLUENT "
"file. Therefore, the output multiblock will only contain the selected zones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/fluentReaderImprovements.md:6
msgid ""
"You can now choose to cache or not the data using the CacheData option. This "
"allows to avoid re-parsing the file to gain IO performances at the expense "
"of a greater memory cost, or the other way around. Because of zone sections "
"interdependency in the FLUENT format, some unselected zone sections may "
"still need to be read from the file, even if they are not part of the output "
"multiblock. Here is the general file parsing logic:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/fluentReaderImprovements.md:9
msgid "If any cell zone is enabled, the whole file needs to be read"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.5/fluentReaderImprovements.md:10
msgid ""
"Otherwise, only the necessary zones are read (nodes, faces, data arrays,...) "
"Therefore, unselecting a zone will not always improve the file's reading "
"time, but will lower the output' size."
msgstr ""
